Parliament, Tuesday, 5 November 2019 – The Standing and Select Committees on Finance will tomorrow, 6 November 2019, hold a joint public hearing on the 2019 Revised Fiscal Framework and Revenue Proposals, also known as the Medium Term Budget Policy Statement (MTBPS). The MTBPS was tabled in the National Assembly on 30 October 2019 by the Minister of Finance, Mr Tito Mboweni, in terms of section 28 of the Public Management Act 1 of 1999 and section 6 (1) of the Money Bills Amendment Procedure and Related Matters Act 9 of 2019. Prior to that, the committee Chairpersons Mr Joe Maswanganyi and Mr Yunus Carrim, had invited stakeholders and other interested parties to forward written submissions to the two committees. They further advised those making written submissions to indicate their interest to make oral presentation in tomorrow’s public hearing. A number of stakeholders responded, including, among others, British American Tobacco, Budget Justice Coalition, Congress of South African Trade Unions, Pietermaritzburg Pensioners Association and Rural Health Advocacy Project. Details of the public hearing are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 6 November 2019
	Venue: Old Assembly Chamber
	Time: 10:00-13:00 ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON FINANCE, MR JOE MASWANGANYI AND SELECT COMMITTEE ON FINANCE, MR YUNUS CARRIM. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact the committees’ Media Officer: Name: Mr Justice Molafo
	Tel: 021 403 8444
	Cell: 081 424 7481
	Email: jmolafo@parliament.gov. Parliament and its committees have the right to ask any institution or person to report to them and may summons any person to appear before them.Read more